==前期生产概念车==
===2006年的雪佛兰科迈罗概念车===
[[File:2006CamaroConcept-001.jpg|thumb]]
该概念轿跑车由南韩人Sangyup Lee所设计。<ref name="DesignedBy">{{cite web |url=http://www.edmunds.com/insideline/do/Features/articleId=109195 |title= Camaro Concept: Like Father, Like Son |accessdate=2008-02-08 |last=Roy |first=Rex |date=2006-02-06 |work=[[Insideline.com|Insideline.com]] |publisher=Edmunds.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chevrolet.co.uk/brochure-service/download?site=GB_en&model=camaro|title=The Chevrolet Camaro|publisher=|accessdate=6 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://online.wsj.com/article/SB121311527578861039.html|title=Korean Car Designers Make Their Mark On the U.S. Auto Industry - Growing Influence in Detroit and Beyond Is Evidenced by Sangyup Lee's Camaro|publisher=|accessdate=6 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.camaro5.com/designer-behind-the-new-camaro-sangyup-lee-profile-interview/|title=Designer behind the new Camaro – Sangyup Lee profile & interview|publisher=|accessdate=6 October 2014}}</ref>该车属于霍顿的GM Zeta平台。该车配置了具有主动燃油管理的400匹马力6.0升 LS2引擎、T56 6前速手动变速箱、采用逐行速率弹簧和气体加压阻尼器的悬挂系统、14英寸转子的四轮通风碟刹，独特的五辐铸造合金轮圈（前轮21英寸，后轮为22英寸），以及275/30R21前轮胎与305/30R22后轮胎。概念车的轴距为{{convert|110.5|in|0|cm|abbr=on}}长，比前代科迈罗长9英寸，而车长为186.2英寸（473厘米），比前代短7英寸。
该车于2006年[[底特律车展|底特律车展]]亮相。<ref name="CamaroConcept">{{cite web |url=http://media.gm.com/us/gm/en/news/events/autoshows/06naias/concepts/06_NAIAS_Chevy_Concept.htm |title=Chevrolet Camaro Concept: Capturing the Timeless Spirit of Camaro |accessdate=2006-12-27 |author=General Motors |date=2006-01-09 |publisher=GM Media Online |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070202021321/http://media.gm.com/us/gm/en/news/events/autoshows/06naias/concepts/06_NAIAS_Chevy_Concept.htm |archivedate=2007-02-02 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref name="RTvideo">{{cite web |url=http://www.roadandtrack.com/article.asp?section_id=15&article_id=3124 |title=World Exclusive: Chevrolet Camaro Concept Video |accessdate=2006-12-27 |last=Hall |first=Jim |date=2006-01-09 |format=WMV |publisher=Road & Track |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070311064911/http://www.roadandtrack.com/article.asp?section_id=15&article_id=3124 |archivedate=2007-03-11 }}</ref><ref name="Patton1">[http://www.americanheritage.com/articles/magazine/ah/2006/6/2006_6_22.shtml Phil Patton] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20071020152554/http://www.americanheritage.com/articles/magazine/ah/2006/6/2006_6_22.shtml |date=2007年10月20日 }} "Retro Car: The Tough Car or the Fun Car?," ''American Heritage'', Nov./Dec. 2006.</ref><ref name="Patton2">{{cite web|url=http://www.autoblog.com/2006/01/09/debut-of-the-chevrolet-camaro-concept/|title=Debut of the Chevrolet Camaro Concept|date=9 January 2006|work=Autoblog|accessdate=6 October 2014}}</ref>

